VESICULAR STOMATITIS, EQUINE - USA (TEXAS)
******************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
Date: Tue, 23 Jun 1998
From: Dorothy Preslar <dpreslar@fas.org>
Source: Office International des Epizooties

The following is the complete report from the OIE Disease Status internet
file of 19 June 1998:
VESICULAR STOMATITIS IN THE UNITED STATES OF AMERICA
See also: 22 May 1998, 24 October 1997, 3 October 1997, 18 July 1997, 11
July 1997, 4 July 1997, 20 June 1997, 13 June 1997
(Date of last previously reported outbreak: 13 May 1998).
Emergency report
Text of a fax received on 18 June 1998 from Dr J.M. Arnoldi, Deputy
Administrator, Veterinary Services, United States Department of
Agriculture, Washington, DC:
Nature of diagnosis: clinical and laboratory.
Date of initial detection of animal health incident: 29 May 1998.
Estimated date of first infection: 25 May 1998.
Location No. of outbreaks
Balmorhea, Reeves County, State of Texas 1

Total number of animals in the outbreak:
species susceptible cases deaths destroyed slaughtered
bov 15 0 0 0 0
equ 7 4 0 0 0

Diagnosis: four of seven horses on the premises exhibited epithelial
erosion of lips; two of these four exhibited epithelial erosions on the tip
and lateral surfaces of the tongue.
A. Laboratory where diagnosis was made: National Veterinary Services
Laboratory, Ames, Iowa.
B. Diagnostic tests used: complement fixation test.
C. Causal agent: vesicular stomatitis virus, Indiana type.
Epidemiology: epidemiological studies in progress.
Control measures during reporting period: quarantine and movement control
inside the country; vesicular stomatitis is a notifiable disease.
--
